namespace Pscf{
namespace Pspc{
/*! 
\page pspc_Domain_page Domain

A Pscf::Pspc::Domain<D> object represents a spatial domain and discretization.
The parameter file format for a Domain is:
\code
Domain{
  unitCell    UnitCell<D>
  mesh        Mesh<D>
  groupName   string
}
\endcode
Parameters and subblocks are described below:
<table>
  <tr>
    <td> unitCell </td>
    <td> Description of a crystallographic unit cell, represented using the text file format for a UnitCell<D> object.
    The text format for a UnitCell contains a string representing the lattice  system (e.g., cubic, orthorhombic, hexagonal, etc.) followed by a list of values for unit cell dimensions and, when needed, angles.
   This format is described in more detail \ref pscf_UnitCell_page "here".
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td> mesh </td>
    <td> 
    A regular discretization mesh, represented as a list of D integers separated by spaces on a single line.
    Component i of this list is the number of grid points along direction i.
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td> groupName </td>
    <td> A string identifier for a crystallographic space group. </td> 
  </tr>
</table>

*/
}
}
